description:
Trade Paperback Release Date: October 2002

Hardcover Release Date: December 2001

All seven issues of the first volume of DANGER GIRL are collected in this sizzling collection that also features the ultra-rare introductory short story from the NEW HORIZONS VOYAGER PACK (originally polybagged with GEN13 Volume One #25). Plus, a complete cover gallery, an amazing sketchbook section, and an introduction by noted actor and DANGER GIRL fan Bruce Campbell (Army of Darkness, Xena)!

Back Blurb

When beautiful adventuress ABBEY CHASE is recruited by the top-secret spy agency known as DANGER GIRL, she buckles up for the ride of her life! Doing battle with an oddball cross-selection of fiends and evil-doers who intend to take over the world, Abbey and her fellow Danger Girls must not only defeat these villains and their diabolical plans--but also do it in the latest skintight fashions of the ultra-sexy super spy!

This is explosive action in exotic locales high adventure laced with mystery and intrigue sexy girls trying to save the world!

This is Danger Girl: The Ultimate Collection

The entire saga in one beautiful volume, complete with extra-special added attractions:

  • Digitally re-mastered coloring, lettering and special effects!
  • Behind the scenes looks at never-before-seen production sketches!
  • Ultra-cool intro by Bruce Campbell!

Danger never looked so good!
name: HC & TPB

description: As Kamui's future visions worsen, other seers and psychics across the nation begin to turn thier eyes toward Tokyo, and the lines between light and dark begin to be drawn...
name: Prelude

description: Haunted by his tragic past, and driven by an awful destiny, Kamui struggles to understand his role in the future to come--a terrible fate to which he and his unique powers are inexorably linked...
name: Overture

description: As Kamui's strange destiny continues to bring sorrow to those around him, other psychics begin to close ranks--the "Seven Seals," who seem to be Kamui's allies, and the "Seven Harbingers" who might be his enemies...
name: Sonata

description: Hinoto herself shows Kamui her vision of the destruction to come. But even though Kamui's future seems to have been predetermined from his very birth, it would seen that his power also comes with a choice--to save the Earth...or to destroy it.
name: Intermezzo

description: More members are added to the Seven Seals--Yuzuriha Nekoi, a young girl accompanied by a dog spirit, and Karen Kasumi, a beautiful woman who can control fire. Meanwhile, Sorata shares a shocking secret with Arashi--that Kamui is not the only one with knowledge of his own predetermined destiny...
name: Serenade

description: Although Kamui has yet to decide what destiny he will pursue, the dance that will soon force his hand has already begun--a deadly duet between light and darkness, between his friends, and his enemies…
name: Duet

description: Kamui's friends and family have been pulled into the deadly orbit of his destiny before--his mother, who died to set him on his path; his aunt, who has also chosen death to provide Kamui with the weapon he will need in the struggle to come; and Kotori, who sees a future from which there is no escape...
name: Rhapsody

description: Past destinies become present when three young men from the CLAMP Academy arrive, a masterful young psychic clashes with his mortal enemy, and the moment of Kamui's destiny finally arrives. But with his decision comes unimaginable tragedy...
name: Crescendo

description: The decision has been made, and sides have finally been chosen, but the cost has been high. A traumatized Kamui needs the kind of healing that only a powerful psychic can provide, and a new battle within his mind is joined...
name: Requiem

description: A startling discovery is made in the depths of the Clamp Academy: Just as Kamui had a twin star, so does the sacred sword! Meanwhile, Hinoto's dreamgazing becomes increasingly disturbing. When Kamui joins her for a session, painful memories are unearthed from deep within his psyche. Can Kamui handle the subsequent flood of emotion?
name: Fugue

description: There's time for reflection as both sides of the conflict regroup: Kamui and other Dragons of Heaven attend school at CLAMP Academy, while Fuma finds his place amoung the Dragons of Earth. But when these two young men, as close as brothers, meet on opposite sides of the battlefield, all hell breaks loose!
name: Interlude

description: Subaru is hospitalized in the aftermath of his showdown against Seiichiro, and Kamui agonizes over his responsibility in this latest disastrous rift between friends. Meanwhile, the Harbingers haven't been standing still--lest we forget, technology is one of the Harbingers' greatest weapons, and it's one that Kamui will soon have to face...
name: Movement

description: Intense conflict leads to heartbreak as the Seven Seals and the Seven Harbingers face off and the casualities begin to pile up. Yuzuriha Nekoi and her dog spirit Inuki face off against expert hacker Satsuki with her supercomputer "The Beast"; Saiki and Kamui have an unfortunate encounter with Fuma; fire-wielder Karen takes on both Seiichiro and Yuto!
name: Lament

description: Duality is a fact of Kamui's prophecy-driven life, but he's not the only one with an evil twin--as the battle between the Dragons of Heaven and Dragons of Earth heats up, this theme is repeated again and again, and both sides of the conflict begin to realize who their opposite numbers are...
name: Concerto

description: Both the Seven Seals and the Seven Harbingers have their reasons for wanting to save the world or destroy it, and the greatest of these is love. For the sake of loved ones long lost, or those not lost yet, decisions are made that will indeed move heaven and earth...
name: Waltz

description: Years of twisted love and bitterness lead at last to a final conflict as longtime rivals Subaru and Seishiro face each other and their own darknesses in a desperate battle on the Rainbow Bridge.
name: Nocturne

description: Tokyo is in a shambles. With Subaru missing and their Dreamseer's predictions foiled, the Seven Seals have decided to roam the city in pairs. Arashi and Yuzuriha must fight for their lives defending Inogashira Park against the Harbinger Satsuki and her monstrous computer, "The Beast," while Kamui and Sorata uncover the horrible truth behind Princess Hinoto.
name: Suite

description: The balance of power is shifting. Arashi's surprising emotional confession to Sorata has unexpected consequences, and the result of Fuma's shocking gift to aimless Subaru is revealed. Unaware of Hinoto's duplicity, Karen and Aoki have followed her instructions and are heading to Ginza to face Tokyo's next threat. Will the Dragons of Heaven win again--and at what cost?
name: Inversion

description: BEST GYMNAST. BEST speller. Best kazoo player. It seems everyone has a talent except Babymouse. That is, until Babymouse takes to the ice and surprises everyone with her spectacular spins and jubilant jumps. Until the famous Olympic coach, Coach Bearnakorva, discovers her and asks Babymouse to be her new protege. Will Babymouse's dreams of a medal come true? Or is she treading on thin ice? Find out in the seventh Babymouse adventure: Skater Girl!
name: Skater Girl

description: Rabbi David Kahn has lived a forty-year lie: he is not, nor has he ever been, Jewish. When at his funeral the truth emerges, the Kahn family must struggle with grief and betrayal as their congregation examines their lives and questions their faith. The eldest son abandons his faith as he gets swept up in an affair with his sister's non-Jewish roommate. Lea, the rebellious sister, reconsiders the religion she has tried so hard to dismiss. The youngest son attempts to somehow return faith and order to his family and community and reinstate his father's good name.
name: GN

description: NEW TITLE!! Now called All Hero Retro Comics!! Dimension- hopping is this issue’s theme, starting out with a “new” retro character, Doctor Dimension!! Set in 1954, the Doctor is smack dab in the middle of a fight with the evil Queen Tygraa, and her cat warriors. Battle along side Doc Dimension, his young friend Chris Carter and guest star Yankee Girl in “Enter Doctor Dimension”. Written and drawn by Bill Black. Part of the second chapter, “Tygraa’s Revenge”, is reworked from a Commando Do story originally published in Paragon Publication’s Fun Comics #1. Then , Doc Dimension acts as narrator on a fantasy story that also deals with interdimensional border-hopping, “Beware The Gem World”, a late-’50′s Charlton story drawn by Steve Ditko. And finally-a story that has NOTHING to do with dimensional changing whatsoever: Magazine Enterprise’s great movie cowboy turned comics star, The Durango Kid in “The Law And The Mask”, reprinted from the mid-1950′s, drawn by Fred Guardineer.
